thread.title: Watch LSU kicker Trent Domingue run a fake FG to a fourth-quarter lead vs. Florida
thread.title_full: Watch LSU kicker Trent Domingue run a fake FG to a fourth-quarter lead vs. Florida | NOLA.com

author: Jerit Roser, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Watch LSU kicker Trent Domingue run a fake FG to a fourth-quarter lead vs. Florida
text:
LSU fans had just finally cut their booing of officials for not calling a pass interference in the end zone on second down.
And Les Miles and company quickly gave a packed Tiger Stadium something to cheer about with a fake field goal two plays later.
Kicker Trent Domingue took the pitch from holder Brad Kragthorpe 16 yards to the end zone, then added an extra point to push the Tigers back ahead, 35-28.
The play made the junior LSU's second-leading rusher at the time, behind star sophomore running back Leonard Fournette.
The Tigers have had a history of utilizing fake field goals against Florida, including the memorable 2010 edition en route to a 33-29 victory in Gainesville, Fla.
